"title": "8369: worthiness",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8369",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Only God truly merits honour and praise but he graciously considers those who humbly serve him with wholehearted devotion to be worthy disciples.</p>\n<h2>God the Father is worthy of honour and praise</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps145:3\">PSA 145:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam22:4\">2SA 22:4</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps18:3\">PSA 18:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr16:25\">1CH 16:25</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps96:4\">PSA 96:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps48:1\">PSA 48:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev4:11\">REV 4:11</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ is worthy of honour and praise</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev5:12\">REV 5:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt3:17\">MAT 3:17</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:11\">MRK 1:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:22\">LUK 3:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:5\">MAT 17:5</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:7\">MRK 9:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:35\">LUK 9:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:9-Phil2:11\">PHP 2:9–2:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:9\">HEB 2:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb3:3\">HEB 3:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet1:17\">2PE 1:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev5:9\">REV 5:9</a></p>\n<h2>People are considered worthy by others</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:4-Luke7:5\">LUK 7:4–7:5</a></strong> <em>Note that the centurion did not consider himself to be worthy (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:7\">Lk 7:7</a>).</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen39:4\">GEN 39:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen41:38-Gen41:40\">GEN 41:38–41:40</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:6\">1SA 16:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs1:42\">1KI 1:42</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan1:18-Dan1:20\">DAN 1:18–1:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan2:46-Dan2:48\">DAN 2:46–2:48</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan3:28-Dan3:30\">DAN 3:28–3:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:11-Acts14:13\">ACT 14:11–14:13</a></p>\n<h2>God considers no person (other than Jesus Christ) to be worthy by nature</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev5:4\">REV 5:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps14:3\">PSA 14:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps143:2\">PSA 143:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl7:20\">ECC 7:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:10-Rom3:12\">ROM 3:10–3:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:23\">ROM 3:23</a></p>\n<h2>Worthiness, like righteousness, is credited to a person by God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess1:11\">2TH 1:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:35\">LUK 20:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:29\">ROM 2:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor10:18\">2CO 10:18</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of people who are considered worthy by God</h2>\n<h3>Those who put God first and deny themselves</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:37-Matt10:38\">MAT 10:37–10:38</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam2:30\">1SA 2:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:62\">LUK 9:62</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:1-Rom12:2\">ROM 12:1–12:2</a></p>\n<h3>Those who suffer persecution for the sake of Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:41\">ACT 5:41</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:10-Matt5:12\">MAT 5:10–5:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess1:5\">2TH 1:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:19-1Pet2:20\">1PE 2:19–2:20</a></p>\n<h3>Those whose lives show Christlike godliness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:10\">COL 1:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:7\">1SA 16:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:1-Eph4:2\">EPH 4:1–4:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess2:12\">1TH 2:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:8-1Tim3:9\">1TI 3:8–3:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:11\">1TI 3:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:2\">TIT 2:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:4\">REV 3:4</a></p>\n<h3>Those who stand firm for the gospel</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:27\">PHP 1:27</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess2:4\">1TH 2:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:15\">2TI 2:15</a></p>\n<h3>Those who are faithful in the use of resources which God has given them</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:21-Matt25:23\">MAT 25:21–25:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:45-Matt24:47\">MAT 24:45–24:47</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:42-Luke12:44\">LUK 12:42–12:44</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:17\">LUK 19:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:17\">1TI 5:17</a></p>\n<h3>Those who welcome God's people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:11\">MAT 10:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:41-Matt10:42\">MAT 10:41–10:42</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom16:2\">ROM 16:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/3John1:6\">3JN 1:6</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of worthy people</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen6:8-Gen6:9\">GEN 6:8–6:9</a> <em>Noah</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut1:36\">DEU 1:36</a> <em>Caleb</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut34:10\">DEU 34:10</a> <em>Moses</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job1:8\">JOB 1:8</a> <em>Job</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan9:23\">DAN 9:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan10:19\">DAN 10:19</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:28\">LUK 1:28</a> <em>Mary</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas2:23\">JAS 2:23</a> <em>Abraham</em></p>",
